        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued April 24 at 5:58AM CDT by NWS Fort Worth TX</headline>
        <description>At 557 AM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 7
miles east of Goldthwaite, or 24 miles northeast of San Saba, moving
northeast at 30 mph.

HAZARD...Winds in excess of 40 mph and half inch hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor damage to outdoor objects is
possible.

This storm will remain over mainly rural areas of southwestern
Hamilton, northeastern Mills and south central Comanche Counties,
including the following locations... Shive, Center City, Energy,
Star, Pottsville, Bozar, Pecan Wells, Indian Gap, and Caradan.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
